.TH LIBSLIRP 3 "2026-05-06" "libslirp 4.7.0" "InterGenOS Library Manual"
.SH NAME
libslirp \- general purpose TCP-IP emulator library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <slirp/libslirp.h>
.PP
.B cc
[\fIflags\fR] \fIfile\fR \fB-lslirp\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBlibslirp\fP is a user-mode networking library used by virtual
machines and containers. It provides a full TCP/IP stack that
operates entirely in userspace without requiring elevated
privileges, kernel modules, or TUN/TAP devices.
.PP
The library implements DHCP, DNS, TFTP, ARP, IPv4, IPv6, ICMP,
TCP, and UDP protocols sufficient to give a guest VM or container
full IP-layer network access through a single socket on the host.
.PP
libslirp is used by QEMU's user-mode networking backend and by
slirp4netns (rootless networking for containers). It replaces the
older slirp implementation that was historically bundled with QEMU.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR slirp4netns (1),
.BR qemu (1)
.PP
Upstream documentation:
.UR https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/slirp/libslirp
.UE .
